==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Home run
<hw>Home" run`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Baseball)</fld>
<def>a complete circuit of the bases made by the batter without being
put out and without an error on the play; also, the hit on which the
batter makes such a circuit; a four-base hit.</def> <note>Most <ex>home
runs</ex> are made when the batter hits a fair ball out of the playing
area on a fly, when the ball cannot be played by the defending team; if
a batter circuits the bases while the ball is still inside the playing
field, it is an <stype>inside-the-park home run</stype>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homeric</ent>⟦br⟧
